Brazil’s ALL Gains Most in Week as Volumes, Earnings Climb

-- B y   A l e x a n d e r   C u a d r o s
-- 
2011-07-22T20:20:13Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-22/brazil-s-all-gains-most-in-week-as-volumes-earnings-climb-1-.html
ALL America Latina Logistica SA (ALLL3) ,
 Latin America ’s largest railroad company, gained the most in
more than a week in Sao Paulo after reporting increases in
volumes and earnings.  ALL rose 1.2 percent to 12.23 reais at 4:15 p.m. New York
time, the most since July 13. The stock had dropped 19 percent
this year through yesterday, compared to a 13 percent decline
for the benchmark Bovespa index.  ALL’s total volume transported rose 8.9 percent in the
second quarter from a year earlier, while earnings before
interest, taxes, depreciation and amortization rose 12.2 percent
to 489 million reais ($315.2 million), according to a regulatory
filing detailing preliminary results. Banco Bradesco SA had
forecast Ebitda of 469 million reais, according to a note to
clients today.  “We view today’s results as slightly positive for ALL,”
Edigimar Maximiliano and Luiz Pecanha, analysts at Bradesco,
wrote in the report. “The company still has an optimistic
outlook for 2011.”  The analysts reiterated their “outperform” rating on the
stock.  To contact the reporter on this story:
